          <floruit when="1678" evidence="internal">He was the twenty fourth abbot of <placeName ref="INS0341">Dabra Libānos</placeName>
                     who succeeded ʿǝč̣č̣age <persName ref="PRS5306Heryaqos">Hǝryāqos</persName> in<date>1678</date>. He was a contemporary of King  
                     <persName ref="PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName> in his  tenure from <date> 1678-1679</date>. He was succeeded by ʿǝč̣č̣age 
                     <persName ref="PRS8325saggaKr">Ṣaggā Krǝstos</persName> in<date>1678</date>.  
                     He was re-appointed in <date>1 september 1686</date> by King  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI">ʾIyāsu I</persName> but he died before he could take the office. 
                     The list of abbots of <placeName ref="INS0341">Dabra Libānos</placeName> refers  that he was the one 
                     who revised the musical notation of <title ref="LIT3178Deggwa">Dǝggʷā</title>. He was also one of the owners of a manuscript containing
                     <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2505Weddas">Wǝddāse ʾAmlāk</ref> and the Marian hymn 
             <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2016Mestir">Mǝśṭira ṣǝgeyāt</ref>.
                  </floruit>
